            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>It is suggested that an extra connector (Part # 2039312C91), completely filled with plugs, be
                        saved and connected to the chassis harness connector when the plowing season is over - this
                        procedure protects against corrosion.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <para>
                <emph type="boldundersc">TESTING:</emph>
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Activate the plow light switch in the dash using the Diamond Logic&#174; Builder
                    software for switch locations.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Turn on vehicle park lights.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Verify that auxiliary connector Cavity E has battery voltage levels present.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Turn ON vehicle headlights to the LOW BEAM position.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Verify that auxiliary connector Cavity C has battery voltage levels present.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Turn vehicle headlights to the HIGH BEAM position.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Verify that auxiliary connector Cavity A has battery voltage levels present.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Turn on vehicle left turn signal.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Verify that auxiliary connector Cavity D has intermittent voltage levels present.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Turn on vehicle right turn signal.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Verify that auxiliary connector Cavity F has intermittent voltage levels present.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Turn off the plow light switch.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Verify all vehicle lights are operating correctly.</para>
            </step1>
            <para>
                <emph type="boldundersc">HOW TO ADD THIS FEATURE:</emph>
            </para>
            <para>There is a plow light kit available 2585355C91 to facilitate installation. The instructions that come
                with the kit are shown below.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>If the vehicle has hydraulic brakes, the instructions for installing relay circuits do not
                        apply as the cavities have factory-installed circuits in the cavities indicated DO NOT REMOVE
                        THESE CIRCUITS, use alternate open cavities. Be sure to mark the function of the added relays on
                        the decal located on the bottom of the PDC cover.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
