        <svcsubproc id="BB08THV">
            <title>08THV - Front Guide Post Lights</title>
            <para>
                <emph type="boldundersc">FEATURE CODE DESCRIPTION:</emph>
            </para>
            <para>08THV - DISCONNECT, FRONT HARNESS for Guide Post Lights; Connectors Located at Headlight Connection,
                for Customer Installation
            </para>
            <para>
                <emph type="boldundersc">FEATURE / BODY FUNCTION:</emph>
            </para>
            <para>This feature provides two additional connectors located in the front wiring harness for front parking
                or identification lights. This feature is commonly used for customer or Body Builder- added guidepost
                lights typically mounted at each end of the front bumper. These connectors come with mating connectors
                and sealing plugs pre-installed. The guide post light circuit is directly tied to the vehicle parking
                light system, so when the headlight switch is turned to the park or on position, these auxiliary lights
                will turn on with the standard vehicle lighting. This feature should be used in any application where
                operation in tight spaces requires constant identification of the vehicle's width.
            </para>
            <para>
                <emph type="boldundersc">SOFTWARE FEATURE CODES / PROGRAMMABLE PARAMETERS:</emph>
            </para>
            <para>Software Feature Codes that must be added: NONE</para>
            <para>Software Feature Codes that must be removed: NONE</para>
            <para>
                <emph type="boldundersc">WIRING INFORMATION:</emph>
            </para>
            <para>Refer to the Circuit Diagram Manual S08322, Chapter 9, Lights, Light System - Marker, Park, Tail,
                Turn, and Stop Lights.
            </para>
